These are the control Constructs which are used to excute instructions Only under given Scenrios.
There are four tyoes of statements.
1. simple-if
2. if-else
3. else -if Ladder
4. Switch-Case

1. simple-if
It executes only under one condition
Syntax: if(condition)
     {
       //Statemnets
     }
Code :
public class kn {
    public static void main(String... args) {
        int a=10;
        if(a>=10){
            System.out.println("hii");

        }
        
    }
}


2.if-else
When the condition is true if bock will excute and when the condition is false else block will be excuted.Only one
block will be excuted at a time for one situation.
Syntax :
if(condtion){
//statemnts
}
else{
//statements
}

code:
public class kn {
    public static void main(String... args) {
        int a=6;
        if(a>=10){
            System.out.println("hii");

        }
        else{
            System.out.println("hello");
        }
        
    }
}

3.else if ladder
It is used when we want specify actions for multiple scenarios.It is excuted from top to bottom and it will execute the
true block condition at first.
if 1st have true condition and after all the blocks will be skipped.
Syntax:
if(condtion){
//statemnts
}
else if{
//statements
}
else if{
//statements
else if{
//statements
.
.
.
.
else{
//Stamts
}


4.Switch Case
It can be executed whwn we want to execute statemnts depending upon specific values.
Syntax:
Switch(value)
{
case value 1:
//stamts
break;
case value 2:
//stamts
break;
case value 3:
//stamts
break;
.
.
.
default:
//stamts
}

